      "message": "gr-button has display:inline-block by default. That is probably not what you want, and I would love to change to display:block for *all* our components. And here you can see why. :-)\n\nBefore the gr-buttons were direct children of a flex box. And if there is nothing between a flex box and an inline element, that it is essentially treated as display:block, because there is no inline context of a parent block. You can verify that by checking the \"Computed\" tab. It shows up as \"display:block\".\n\nAfter your change gr-buttons are wrapped into gr-tooltip-content. gr-tooltip-content has \"display:inline\" by default (as all custom components), but again that does not matter much here, because as a direct child of a flex box, gr-tooltip-content will be treated as \"display:block\", see \"Computed\". But gr-button is now treated as an inline element within its parent and the quirks of the default vertical-align:baseline kick in, which is the culprit is 90% of the cases when you deal with vertical misalignment. The alternative for fixing this issue is to vertical-align:top elements like buttons. That would also work here.",
